    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Performances that include trained animal acts or exhibitions of human skill and daring, or both. Circuses usually include a trained, traveling company or troupe of performers, various animals, and their equipage. The term "circus" refers to the circular arena surrounded by tiers of seats below which the performance occurs in a circular area called the "ring."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>包含馴獸表演，或展現人體技巧與膽量的演出，或兼具兩者。馬戲表演通常有一個訓練有素的巡迴演出劇團，或一團表演工作者、各種動物以及其所需之裝備。「馬戲團」一詞指在多層座位所圍出的圓形表演場地「馬戲場」，表演就在這座位下方的圓形區域演出。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Performances que incluem atos de animais treinados ou exibições de habilidade e ousadia humana, ou ambos. Os circos geralmente incluem uma companhia ou trupe de artistas treinados e viajantes, vários animais e seus equipamentos. O termo "circo" se refere à arena circular cercada por fileiras de assentos abaixo da qual a apresentação ocorre em uma área circular chamada de "picadeiro".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
